# ERP docs & extra-features sync

When you **add, change, or remove** any user-facing feature, admin capability, feature flag, migration, or cross-module behavior, update **all applicable** docs in the same session — do not leave docs stale.

## Friend docs (update what applies)

| Doc | When to update |
|-----|----------------|
| `PROGRESS_INDEX.md` | Always — §2 status, §3 flags, §6 gaps, §7 next step, §8 migrations |
| `docs/EXTRA_FEATURES.md` | User-requested or non-PRD extras (one row per feature) |
| `01_BUILD_PROMPT.md` | New §4 appendix block (e.g. §4.R, §4.S) with paths + behavior |
| `03_AI_INDEX_RULES.md` | Only if the maintenance protocol itself changes |
| `docs/<MODULE>_FLOW.md` | Flow changes (procurement, sales, inventory) |
| `src/lib/mock-data/feature-flags.ts` | New `feat_*` / `mod_*` flag definitions |

## Minimum PROGRESS_INDEX updates

1. **§2** — module row: status + ≤15 word note  
2. **§3** — checkbox or bullet if new feature flag  
3. **§6** — strike done gaps; add new gaps  
4. **§7** — one actionable next task  
5. **§8** — new migration filename when schema changes  

## Extra-features entry format (`docs/EXTRA_FEATURES.md`)

```markdown
| Feature | Flag / setting | Key paths | Added |
```

Include: admin toggle location, API/server entry points, main UI routes.

## 01_BUILD_PROMPT appendix format

Add under `# 4.X <Title>` at end of build prompt (before closing line):

- **What** (1–2 sentences)  
- **Admin / flag** (if any)  
- **Key files** (table of paths)  
- **Wired on** (which list pages / modules)  

## Do not

- Document only in chat — always persist to files above  
- Duplicate full PRD text — reference `02_PRD.md` IDs where relevant  
- Add features without `feat_*` flag when behavior is optional and admin-controlled  
